xciting things we are doing  Just click on the topic headings for the full story  With warm regards  Floyd H  Duncan  Col  Department Chairman AACSB Accreditation This past Christmas I was checking my VMI email account from home when I discovered a Christmas present I had been waiting on for years  The Major Field Test in Business Though not up to our usual standards  the Class of 2010 performed well on the Educational Testing Service s Major Field Test Business  MFTB  Faculty Research Our faculty have been hard at work publishing research in academic journals as well as presenting their research at various conferences around the country and the world  Lopez Chair The Economics and Business department is pleased to announce the appointment of Mr  Stephen Todd McCane to teach in the department for Fall 2010  Experiential Learning As part of a course titled  The Chilean Miracle  International Marketing and Business  eight cadets and five students from Va Tech  lead by Col  Joe Scarpaci  travelled to Chile not only to learn about economics and business  but also about the country s culture  The Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfolio managers  Cadet Internships In the summer of 2010  thirteen cadets will be participating in internships at various businesses across the country  Four of these cadets are also doing the associated academic work required to earn business or economic elective credits for their internships  Richmond Federal Reserve Bank Field Trip On April 6  2010  Maj  Allen traveled with 9 cadets to Richmond to tour the Federal Reserve Bank  SBD and ODE Activity The Sigma Beta Delta  the Honor Society for Business and Omicron Delta Economics Honor Society were quite active this past year thanks to cadet leadership  Beta Gamma Sigma As an AACSB accredited program  VMI was invited to create a new chapter of the Beta Gamma Sigma business honor society  Cadet Awards The Annual ODE Banquet to honor our top cadets was held on April 22nd  Alumni Survey Calling all members of the Classes of 1995 and 2005  Stay Connected to ECBU Please let us know what you ve been up to by emailing us at ECBUnewsletter vmi edu or look us up on Facebook  search for  VMI Economics and Business  and Twitter  VMIECBU  If you are interested in hosting a field trip  accepting an intern  speaking to our cadets or helping out in any way at all  just let us know  Even if you have nothing to report  send an email to let us know that you want to be on our email list  Spring 2010 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Field Test  Faculty Research  Lopez Chair  Experiential Learning  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  FED Reserve Field Trip  SBD   ODE Activity  Beta Gamma Sigma  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 